cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with stereo vision and image matching. The use of a deep architecture and training the network in an end-to-end fashion suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The normalization technique introduced in the paper could also make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of camera intrinsics and recovering the relative pose suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
